---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import TimezoneAbbreviationsList from '../components/TimezoneAbbreviationsList.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Time Zone Abbreviations — GMT, EST, PST & More | Clockr"
	description="Look up common time zone abbreviations — GMT, UTC, EST, PST, CET, IST, JST, AEST, and more. Searchable reference with UTC offsets and regions."
	category="timezones"
>
	<div class="tza-page">
		<div class="tza-header">
			<div class="tza-eyebrow">
				<span class="tza-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				TIME ZONES
			</div>
			<h1 class="tza-title">
				<span class="tza-gradient">Time Zone Abbreviations</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="tza-subtitle">Common time zone abbreviations and their meanings</p>
		</div>

		<TimezoneAbbreviationsList client:load />

		<section class="tza-how">
			<h2 class="tza-section-title">About time zone abbreviations</h2>
			<div class="tza-how-card">
				<p>
					Time zone abbreviations are short letter codes — like EST, GMT, or JST
					— that label a region&apos;s standard or daylight offset from UTC.
					They make flight schedules, broadcast listings, and email timestamps
					easier to read than spelling out full zone names every time. Most
					abbreviations are three or four letters, often ending in &ldquo;ST&rdquo;
					(standard time) or &ldquo;DT&rdquo; (daylight time).
				</p>
				<p>
					The problem is that abbreviations were never assigned globally. Many
					letter combinations are reused in different countries — CST can mean
					Central Standard Time in North America or China Standard Time in East
					Asia; IST can mean Indian Standard Time, Irish Standard Time, or Israel
					Standard Time. That is why this page lists ambiguous codes as separate
					entries with their full names, and why serious scheduling should always
					include a city or IANA zone name (such as
					<code>America/New_York</code>) rather than an abbreviation alone.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="tza-faq">
			<h2 class="tza-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="tza-faq-list">
				<details class="tza-faq-item">
					<summary class="tza-faq-question"
						>What&apos;s the difference between GMT and UTC?</summary
					>
					<div class="tza-faq-answer">
						<p>
							GMT (Greenwich Mean Time) is a time zone based on the sun&apos;s
							position at Greenwich, London. UTC (Coordinated Universal Time) is
							the modern global reference kept by atomic clocks. In everyday use
							they both represent offset zero and are often used
							interchangeably, but UTC is the technically correct term for the
							international standard. See our UTC/GMT Converter for live
							conversions.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tza-faq-item">
					<summary class="tza-faq-question"
						>Why do some abbreviations mean different things in different countries?</summary
					>
					<div class="tza-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Abbreviations grew organically within each country before global
							coordination was common. There is no central registry that assigns
							unique three-letter codes worldwide, so collisions are inevitable.
							When you see IST, always check the full name and region — Indian
							Standard Time (UTC+5:30) and Irish Standard Time (UTC+1) share the
							same letters but are six and a half hours apart.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tza-faq-item">
					<summary class="tza-faq-question"
						>What is the difference between EST and EDT?</summary
					>
					<div class="tza-faq-answer">
						<p>
							EST (Eastern Standard Time) is UTC−5, used in winter in the US and
							Canadian east. EDT (Eastern Daylight Time) is UTC−4, used during
							daylight saving from spring through autumn. The same pattern
							applies across US zones: CST/CDT, MST/MDT, and PST/PDT each shift
							by one hour when clocks spring forward.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tza-faq-item">
					<summary class="tza-faq-question"
						>Should I use abbreviations when scheduling international meetings?</summary
					>
					<div class="tza-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Abbreviations are fine as shorthand among people who share the same
							region, but for international calls always specify the city and
							UTC offset — or use our Time Zone Meeting Planner. An email saying
							&ldquo;3 pm CST&rdquo; could mean Chicago, Beijing, or Havana
							depending on context.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tza-faq-item">
					<summary class="tza-faq-question"
						>Do all countries use daylight saving time?</summary
					>
					<div class="tza-faq-answer">
						<p>
							No. Hawaii, Arizona (most areas), Japan, South Korea, China, and
							many countries near the equator keep the same offset year-round.
							Others switch between standard and daylight variants seasonally.
							This reference lists both where they are commonly searched.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="tza-related">
			<h3 class="tza-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="tza-related-grid">
				<a href="/world-clock" class="tza-related-card"
					><span class="tza-related-name">World Clock</span></a
				>
				<a href="/timezone-converter" class="tza-related-card"
					><span class="tza-related-name">Timezone Converter</span></a
				>
				<a href="/utc-gmt-converter" class="tza-related-card"
					><span class="tza-related-name">UTC/GMT Converter</span></a
				>
				<a href="/time-zones" class="tza-related-card"
					><span class="tza-related-name">All Time Zone Tools</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.tza-tool {
		margin-bottom: 56px;
	}

	.tza-controls {
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	.tza-search-label {
		display: block;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		margin-bottom: 10px;
	}

	.tza-search {
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 14px 18px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: #fff;
		outline: none;
		margin-bottom: 12px;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			box-shadow 0.2s ease;
	}

	.tza-search:focus {
		border-color: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.55);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 153, 255, 0.12);
	}

	.tza-search::placeholder {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.tza-count {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.tza-empty {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		text-align: center;
		padding: 32px 16px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.tza-table-wrap {
		overflow-x: auto;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
	}

	.tza-table {
		width: 100%;
		border-collapse: collapse;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
	}

	.tza-table thead {
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.2);
	}

	.tza-table th {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.75);
		text-align: left;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.tza-table td {
		padding: 14px 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
		line-height: 1.5;
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
		vertical-align: top;
	}

	.tza-table tbody tr:hover {
		background: rgba(0, 153, 255, 0.04);
	}

	.tza-abbr {
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.tza-abbr-code {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 800;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tza-ambig-badge {
		display: inline-block;
		margin-left: 8px;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 9px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 193, 7, 0.95);
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 193, 7, 0.35);
		border-radius: 999px;
		padding: 2px 7px;
		vertical-align: middle;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.tza-name {
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		min-width: 180px;
	}

	.tza-offset {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.9);
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.tza-region {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		min-width: 160px;
	}

	.tza-disclaimer {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		line-height: 1.6;
		text-align: center;
		margin: 20px 0 0;
		max-width: 640px;
		margin-inline: auto;
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.tza-table th:nth-child(4),
		.tza-table td:nth-child(4) {
			min-width: 140px;
		}
	}
</style>

<style>
	.tza-page {
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px 80px;
	}

	.tza-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.tza-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tza-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.tza-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 56px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -2px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tza-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tza-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.tza-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tza-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.tza-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.tza-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.tza-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.tza-how-card code {
		font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.85);
	}

	.tza-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.tza-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.tza-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.tza-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tza-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.tza-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tza-faq-item[open] .tza-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.tza-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.tza-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.tza-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.tza-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tza-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.tza-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	.tza-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.tza-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.4);
	}

	.tza-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}
</style>
